ollowers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2011-02-21T22:12:11Z","updated_at":"2011-02-21T22:12:11Z","body":"Thinking about this some more, it seems like the transactions should actually be implemented with throw/catch, which is better able to circumvent exception handling implemented in the submitted proc :)\n","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/comments/795067/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"dchelimsky","id":1075,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwNzU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1075?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky","html_url":"https://github.com/dchelimsky","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dchelimsky/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/comments/795090","html_url":"https://github.com/rspec/rspec-core/issues/322#issuecomment-795090","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/322","id":795090,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDc5NTA5MA==","user":{"login":"jfirebaugh","id":98601,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk4NjAx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/98601?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh","html_url":"https://github.com/jfirebaugh","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2011-02-21T22:16:40Z","updated_at":"2011-02-21T22:16:40Z","body":"> all exceptions are caught and reported on, but not bubbled up\n\nIf this is true of exceptions due to should failures as well, perhaps my initial analysis was wrong.\n\nThis is my around hook:\n\n```\naround(:each) do |example|\n  db.transaction do\n    example.run\n    raise Sequel::Rollback\n  end\nend\n```\n\nIt's possible that rollbacks always happen due to the `raise Sequel::Rollback`, not due to the propagation of an exception out of `example.run`.\n\nIn that case, the issue is that throw/catch bypasses `raise Sequel::Rollback`. If I don't need to worry about letting exceptions raised by `example.run` propagate, I could write the hook like this:\n\n```\naround(:each) do |example|\n  db.transaction do\n    begin\n      example.run\n    ensure\n      raise Sequel::Rollback\n    end\n  end\nend\n```\n\nStill, I wouldn't expect to have to write it like this. Given the original definition of the hook, wouldn't switching to exceptions still work, despite their not being bubbled up?\n","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/comments/795090/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"jfirebaugh","id":98601,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk4NjAx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/98601?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh","html_url":"https://github.com/jfirebaugh","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jfirebaugh/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-core/issues/comments/795108","html_url":"https://github.com/rspec/rspec-core/issues/322#issuecomment-795108","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rspec/rspec-